  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Surfshark is a consumer VPN and digital privacy service founded in 2018 and headquartered in Amsterdam, Netherlands, with additional offices in Vilnius and Kaunas, Lithuania, Warsaw, Poland, and Berlin, Germany. In 2022 Surfshark merged with Nord Security, though the two brands continue to operate as separate products with independent apps, server infrastructure, and pricing. Surfshark operates a network of more than 4,500 servers across roughly 100 countries and allows unlimited simultaneous device connections on every plan, which differentiates it from many competing VPN services that cap device counts. Core features include AES encryption and IP masking, an ad and cookie pop-up blocker, rotating IP addresses, and a double VPN mode for extra encryption layers. The service is sold on three subscription tiers billed mainly as 24-month plans with bonus months: Starter (VPN plus ad blocking), Surfshark One (adds an antivirus suite), and Surfshark One+ (adds Surfshark Alert identity and data breach monitoring, plus Incogni personal data removal). Starter pricing begins around 2.29 euros per month on the long-term plan, with higher rates for shorter one-month or one-year commitments. All plans include a 30-day money-back guarantee and a free trial period. Surfshark's no-logs policy has been independently audited, and the company reports over 4,500 servers across around 100 countries. It is best suited for individuals and families who want unlimited-device VPN coverage plus optional bundled antivirus or identity protection.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
